Asymptomatic isolated partial hiatal herniation of the pancreas: MDCT evaluation and anatomical explanation: case report and review of literature. Isolated herniation of the pancreas through a gastroesophageal hiatus is an extremely rare condition, and only one case has been reported in the world literature. We describe a MDCT diagnosis of isolated partial hiatal hernia containing the body of a normal pancreas in an asymptomatic patient, give an anatomical explanation and review the corresponding literature.